HEADWORD: Luke
<hw>Luke</hw> <pr>(l⟦umac⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Prob. fr.
<ets>lew</ets>, perh. influenced by AS. <ets>wl⟦ae⟧c</ets> warm,
lukewarm, remiss. Cf. Lew.]</ety> <def>Moderately warm; not hot; tepid;
lukewarm.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Luke"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nine penn'orth o'brandy and water <qex>luke</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lukewarm</ent>⟦br⟧
